            <img src="images/pawn.jpg" alt="Pawn Piece" class="piece-image">
            <p>The pawn is the most numerous piece in chess, typically starting in the second row. It moves forward one square at a time, but captures diagonally. On its first move, a pawn can move two squares forward. If it reaches the opposite end of the board, it can be promoted to another piece (except the king).</p>
